    "summary": "The user asks for an economic breakdown of immigration, probes whether wage depression claims are myths, and then asks if there is a media bias that favors \"pro-immigration\" arguments as facts while dismissing \"anti-immigration\" arguments as fear-based. The assistant provides a neutral overview of the economic arguments, acknowledges the complexity of wage-related studies, and confirms that media framing can indeed lead to the polarization and biased presentation the user suggested.",
